valuation_premium.description: Alphabet trading at a premium compared to historical averages; any sign of slowing Cloud momentum or Search revenue miss due to AI disruption could lead to correction

free_cash_flow_weakening.description: Seeking Alpha analyst downgraded citing valuation concerns and weakening free cash flow

key_analyst_quotes.quote: This quarterly report continued a trend that started in late summer 2025 with Alphabet demonstrating continued operating momentum in its core business while scaling its consumer and enterprise AI efforts.

data_quality_notes.price_target_variance: Different aggregators show different averages ($330-$375) due to varying analyst pools, recency weighting, and inclusion criteria. StockAnalysis.com (43 analysts, $346.21) used as primary source.
data_quality_notes.revenue_estimate_variance: Consensus FY2026 revenue ranges from $455B (Trefis individual) to $467.92B (StockAnalysis consensus). Goldman Sachs at $472.2B.
data_quality_notes.eps_estimate_note: FY2026 consensus EPS of $11.55 vs Goldman Sachs at $10.66 GAAP EPS - difference may reflect GAAP vs non-GAAP methodology.
data_quality_notes.capex_impact_on_estimates: Post-Q4 2025 earnings, analyst estimates may still be updating to reflect the $175-185B capex guidance. Data collected within 2 days of earnings release.
data_quality_notes.quarterly_eps_gaps: Only Q1 2026 quarterly EPS estimate ($2.61) available; Q2-Q4 2026 quarterly estimates not found in searches.
